title: Murtazaliev vs Tszyu HIGHLIGHTS: October 19, 2024 | PBC on Prime Video
description:
Undefeated IBF Super Welterweight World Champion Bakhram Murtazaliev dropped former world champion Tim Tszyu four times on his way to a third-round stoppage in the main event of PBC Championship Boxing on Prime Video action Saturday night from the Caribe Royale Resort in Orlando, Florida.
 
After winning the title in his opponent‚Äôs home territory of Germany earlier this year, Murtazaliev (23-0, 17 KOs) made a statement by dropping Tszyu (24-2, 17 KOs) early and often on his way to the dominant stoppage.
 
The first knockdown came in round two with a strong counter left hook sending Tszyu to the canvas. Tszyu showed the incredible grit that‚Äôs made him a superstar in his native Australia to rise to his feet, but was ultimately sent back to the ground two more times in the round.
 
"We just worked on these combinations all the time and when the fight came, it was automatic,‚Äù said Murtazaliev. ‚ÄúWe worked for 10 weeks on those punches that hurt him. We created opportunities and we believed that we could win this fight.‚Äù
 
Continuing to press forward and look for moments in round three, Murtazaliev landed another vicious counter left hand that scored him his fourth knockdown in less than three rounds. While Tszyu continued to battle back, the onslaught from Murtazaliev proved to be too much as Tszyu‚Äôs corner threw in the towel, ending the fight 1:55 into the round.
 
"When I landed that first big shot, I knew how hard it was,‚Äù said Murtazaliev. ‚ÄúTszyu is a real warrior and I hope one day we can work together and spar and help each other to grow."
 
"Every time I step into the ring I leave it all in there,‚Äù said Tszyu. ‚ÄúThings didn't go to plan and the better man won tonight. No excuses. After the first shot, things started not going according to plan. That's part of boxing, you get hit and reactions get slower. Bakhram is the man at 154."

description:
Wild Life: Episode 1 - ANYTHING COULD HAPPEN!

Welcome to WILD LIFE the next season in the Wild Life series. This time, there will be a different twist that affects the game every session/episode (only one person episode). The twists may or may not present some danger to the participants. 

This season, we have 6 lives. 4-6 Lives you have a dark green name. 3 lives you have a lime green name. 2 lives you have a yellow name and on your last and final life, you turn hostile and red. The last player standing, wins. Dark green names are able to have lives stolen from them when killed by a red or yellow life. Only Red names can kill anyone. 

There are lots of little details to be revealed as the series goes on.

title: Wolf Man | Official Trailer
description:
What if someone you loved became something else? #WolfManMovie only in theaters January 17.

---
From Blumhouse and visionary writer-director Leigh Whannell, the creators of the chilling modern monster tale The Invisible Man, comes a terrifying new lupine nightmare: Wolf Man. 

Golden Globe nominee Christopher Abbott (Poor Things, It Comes at Night) stars as Blake, a San Francisco husband and father, who inherits his remote childhood home in rural Oregon after his own father vanishes and is presumed dead. With his marriage to his high-powered wife, Charlotte (Emmy winner Julia Garner; Ozark, Inventing Anna), fraying, Blake persuades Charlotte to take a break from the city and visit the property with their young daughter, Ginger (Matlida Firth; Hullraisers, Coma).

But as the family approaches the farmhouse in the dead of night, they‚Äôre attacked by an unseen animal and, in a desperate escape, barricade themselves inside the home as the creature prowls the perimeter. As the night stretches on, however, Blake begins to behave strangely, transforming into something unrecognizable, and Charlotte will be forced to decide whether the terror within their house is more lethal than the danger without. 

The film co-stars Sam Jaeger (The Handmaid‚Äôs Tale), Ben Prendergast (The Sojourn Audio Drama) and Benedict Hardie (The Invisible Man). 

Wolf Man is directed by Whannell, whose previous films with Blumhouse include The Invisible Man, Upgrade and Insidious: Chapter 3. The screenplay is written by Leigh Whannell & Corbett Tuck, Lauren Schuker Blum & Rebecca Angelo (Dumb Money). 

The film is produced by Blumhouse founder and CEO Jason Blum and is executive produced by Ryan Gosling, Ken Kao, Bea Sequeira, Mel Turner and Leigh Whannell. Wolf Man is a Blumhouse and Motel Movies production.

title: It Turns Out, Hybrids Are Really Hard On Engines
description:
Hybrid vehicles are uniquely challenging due to the frequent engine start/stops, as well as lower overall engine temperatures, which can lead to water and fuel dilution.
Sponsored by Mobil 1 ‚Äì https://www.mobil.com/en/lubricants/ 

Hybrid vehicles are a great solution to improving fuel economy, but they have their own unique challenges. Because hybrid engines start & stop frequently, this often results in lower engine temperatures, which in turn can create issues with water and fuel dilution. Frequent start/stops, water, and fuel, can all create problems that exacerbate engine wear. 

To combat this, Mobil 1 has developed Mobil 1 hybrid, a full synthetic motor oil that is designed to meet the challenges that hybrid vehicles place on engines. This video will focus on three main subjects: how hybrids work, why hybrids are hard on engines, and what solutions exist to combat these challenges.

title: The Sims 4 Life & Death: Official Gameplay Trailer
description:
The Sims‚Ñ¢ 4 Life & Death Expansion Pack* arrives Oct 31 and is available for pre-order now: https://www.ea.com/games/the-sims/the-sims-4/store/addons/the-sims-4-life-and-death-expansion-pack  

Order now through Dec 12 for the Macabre Mementos Digital Content**; the Lasting Legacy Family Portrait, Mournful Melodies Music Box, and Plumed Elegance Mask.

Peel back the veil: https://www.ea.com/games/the-sims/the-sims-4/store/addons/the-sims-4-life-and-death-expansion-pack  

Sims can collect Bucket List goals and earn rewards for completing them ‚Äì but don't worry if they can't! If a Sim dies with Unfinished Business they can still live(?) their dreams as a Ghost, and still earn rewards. The ultimate reward for completing Bucket Lists and Unfinished Business is Rebirth.

For Sims who want to live life on the dark side there are two new careers; an off-screen Mortician career and an active Reaper career which will let you go work for Grim at his secret office as well as travel to reap souls.

There's a lot of eerie fun to get into off the clock as well. Explore Crypts, build your Thanatlogy skill, collect tarot cards, and even adopt a Pet Crow.

Death affects different Sims in different ways. Create fully custom Grieving Rituals and decorate Caskets and Gravesites according to the wishes of the departed Sim or their loved ones. There are 4 types of grief which Sims may experience depending on their personalities and their relationship to the deceased.

Sims can also prepare for their own deaths in life by creating Wills and deciding who to pass on Heirlooms, assets, and children should they pass away.

The journey doesn't end with death. Sims can continue on as Ghosts and even learn new supernatural powers. Ghosts who are helpful while haunting will earn Goodwill essence while Ghosts who think it's fun to be frightening will earn Fear essence. Both essences can be sold for Simoleans.

Embrace the Macabre (one of 3 new traits!) in Life & Death.

Available October 31 at 10AM PT on EA App PC/Mac, Steam, Xbox One, Xbox Series X|S, PlayStation¬Æ4, and PlayStation¬Æ5. Pre-order now: https://www.ea.com/games/the-sims/the-sims-4/store/addons/the-sims-4-life-and-death-expansion-pack

*Requires The Sims 4 & all game updates. For PC, see minimum system requirements for the pack.

**Conditions and restrictions apply. See https://www.ea.com/games/the-sims/the-sims-4/store/addons/the-sims-4-life-and-death-expansion-pack

description:
Two trees cleaved through my house after Hurricane Helene blew through my mountain home of Asheville. While I‚Äôve shown that the damage to the structure is intense, many have asked what happened to the LGR retro collection, vintage computers, video games and such. So here‚Äôs an update!

Of course the most important thing to me is that myself, my family, and my friends here are safe. But I am also deeply thankful it was not any worse in terms of items destroyed or damaged. The majority of old hardware and software survived, and LGR videos (eventually) will continue!

title: I LOST MY BROTHER | THE WORLD LOST A LEGEND | BUT NO ONE LOST AS MUCH AS HIS SWEET FAMILY
description:
It is with broken hearts we share the untimely passing of our hero, Justin Bingham. The world lost a legend. His family lost their rock. Lindsay lost the love of her life. Their children have lost their best friend. But we have not lost hope. Justin loved life more than anything. His passion for living was rivaled only by his devotion to his family. His wife and his four precious kids were his reason for living, the reason he got out of bed every morning and his sole purpose on earth.

He never would have wanted to leave them this way but we pray that he can see the armies of earthly angels surrounding his family at this most desolate time. There are no words to describe the pain or confusion we are all feeling right now, but if you knew Justin you know he would infuse this moment with optimism and positivity. He‚Äôd grab this agony by the horns and ride it through the impending storm with his family on his back. So we pick up the pieces. We remember him. We honor him. We lean on his strength. And we find a way. We move forward with faith, however impossible it may seem, and look forward to the day we are together again.

We are eternally grateful for the outpouring of love and support the family has already received. For those who wish to pay their respects and anyone looking to be inspired by his exemplary life you can find more information on his obituary page: https://www.andersonmortuary.com/obituaries/justin-bingham
